Class IOManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • lib.runDetails.IOManager

  • public class IOManager
extends java.lang.Object
    this is factory class provide various method to create object of IntIODetail. this class provide facility to create object of IntIODetail. it also provide facility of writing and reading IntIODetail objects to and from file.

    Neel Patel

      • getIODetail

        public static IntIODetail getIODetail(java.nio.file.Path dir,
                                      long pid,
                                      long index,
                                      boolean isComp)
                               throws java.io.IOException
        this method return object of IntIODetail from the directory specified by path. this method resolve the file path using specified parameters using standard naming convention. after the resolving the file path it call the method IntIODetail getIODetail(Path filepath,boolean isComp) with proper parameters. this method read the object of type IntIODetail. form file specified by dir. the path specified by dir must be absolute. this method throw IOException if path is invalid or file not found or invalid format or object can not be deserialize because of version difference of corresponding class.
        Parameters:
        dir - path object specifying the valid path of the directory in which file exist with proper naming convention which contain object.
        pid - programID
        index - index of test-case
        isComp - is boolean, if it is true then the object will be decrypted before read, otherwise the object will be read from file as it.
        Returns:
        object of type IntIODetail read from specified dir. null if any invalid parameters or data found.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if the error occur while reading object from file.

      • writeIntIODetail

        public static boolean writeIntIODetail(IntIODetail obj,
                                       java.nio.file.Path dir)
        write the object in separate file in the directory specified by the path object dir. return true if the object is written successfully otherwise return false. the path specified by dir must be absolute. the new file is created in the directory specified by dir with the formated name as follows..
        vVpPiI.data where 'V' specify the version of the class if available, otherwise 'NA', 'P' specify the programID if available, otherwise 'NA', 'I' specify the index if available, otherwise 'NA'.
        Parameters:
        obj - object to be written in file.
        dir - directory in which the object is to be written.
        Returns:
        true if the object written in file successfully, false otherwise.

      • writeIntIODetail

        public static boolean writeIntIODetail(IntIODetail obj,
                                       java.nio.file.Path dir,
                                       boolean comp)
        write the object in separate file in the directory specified by the path object dir after compressing. comp is false then the this method works same as boolean writeIntIODetail(IntIODetail obj,Path dir). return true if the object is written successfully otherwise return false. the path specified by dir must be absolute. the new file is created in the directory specified by dir with the formated name as follows..
        cvVpPiI.data where 'V' specify the version of the class if available, otherwise 'NA', 'P' specify the programID if available, otherwise 'NA', 'I' specify the index if available, otherwise 'NA'.
        Parameters:
        obj - object to be written in file.
        dir - directory in which the object is to be written.
        comp - is boolean, if it is true then the object will be compressed before written, otherwise the writeIntIODetail is called with obj and dir.
        Returns:
        true if the object written in file successfully, false otherwise.
